The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, May 25, 2004 				 Books knock on the door
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Come monsoon, and Howrah is to get its own mobile library, thanks to Howrah Citizens Forum, a social welfare organisation.																								State minister for libraries Nemai Mal has lauded the proposal and we should be able to flag off the library in a month, said Nisith Sarkar, forum convener.																								An initial investment of Rs 15,000 will be borne entirely by the organisation. The library will later be handed over to Ramakrishna Granthagar, in Belur, for maintenance and subsequent stock upgrades.																								The library will debut on June 25 with 300 books. Membership is not mandatory, but readers can borrow books for Rs 2. 																								The book will have to be returned in 15 days and a representative of the library will collect it from the readers doorstep, forum members said. 																								There are 135 state-run libraries in Howrah, but not enough readers. The forum intends to fan geNext interest in books and our aim is to reach 100 readers a day, convener Sarkar signed off.
